
[1]scorner

   SCORN'ER, n.

   1. One that scorns; a contemner; a despiser.

   They are great scorners of death.

   2. A scoffer; a derider; in Scripture, one who scoffs at religion, its
   ordinances and teachers, and who makes a mock of sin and the judgments
   and threatenings of God against sinners. Prov. 1. Prov. 19.
